    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT393-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi alar malivu varaitta (C2, G2:
                    malivuraittu) varaivu kaṭāyatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante inquiring about marriage,
                    uttering joy about the gossip, while HE is behind the hedge. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT393">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> mayaṅkumalark kōtai kuḻaiya makiḻnaṉ</l>
                    <l> muyaṅkiya nāṭavac cilavē yalarē</l>
                    <l> kūkaik kōḻi vākaip paṟantalaip</l>
                    <l> pacumpūṭ pāṇṭiyaṉ viṉaiva latikaṉ</l>
                    <l> kaḷiṟoṭu paṭṭa ñāṉṟai</l>
                    <l> yoḷiṟuvāṭ koṅka rārppiṉum peritē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l> Very few [were] the days the delightful man embraced [me],</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> for the garland of intertwined blossoms to soften.</l>
                    <l rend="indent9"> The gossip,</l>
                    <l> it [is] louder than the roaring of the Koṅkars with bright swords,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> when the energetic Atikaṉ, the Pāṇṭiya with green ornaments ,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> fell with the elephant bull,</l>
                    <l rend="indent3"> in the desert place of Vākai [full of] owls [and] fowl .</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
